## The fix (what the diff does)
- patchRunnerClass: the runAsync/runEphemeral wrapper changed from a plain
  function returning the original generator to an `async function*` that records
  each yielded event's invocationId and, in a `finally`, calls
  finishInterruptedInvocations(this, ids). The finally runs on normal
  completion, early break/return, throw, or abort.
- WeaveAdkPlugin: afterRunCallback refactored to share a private endInvocation()
  helper; new public idempotent finishInterruptedInvocation(invocationId) marks
  the run interrupted. finishInterruptedInvocations() (module fn) resolves the
  plugin via runner.pluginManager.getPlugin(WEAVE_ADK_PLUGIN_NAME) and narrows
  to the method (CJS/ESM instanceof is unreliable).
- AdkEvent gains invocationId?: string.
- Also documents the H2 SSE NonProgressiveStrategy limitation in a comment (text
  + tool call in one turn split across two non-partial responses; tool call
  still captured as its own execute_tool span; default streamingMode NONE is
  unaffected). No behavior change for H2 — documentation only.

